New Jersey Devils assistant Adam
Oates has been named coach of the  Washington Capitals , the
National Hockey League team said in a statement.  Oates replaces Dale Hunter, who chose not to return to the
franchise after it was eliminated from the playoffs.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
